Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of place recognition for mobile robots and self-driving vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of omnidirectional vision sensors and image processing techniques suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as well. The formulation of the problem as a sparse convex optimization problem indicates a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents a new dataset and analysis, which could be relevant to the computer vision and pattern recognition community (cs.CVPR).
